This program is meant to provide information on how well a given comparison raster file matches a reference raster file. 
The main use case for this is comparing data from a landcover classification algorithm used on satellite or aerial imagery 
to ground truth data. The raster files are expected to have values representing landcover classifications, usually these will 
be a subset of numbers between 0-99. The user also provides a csv file that is a landcover classification key containing the 
numerical land cover class values and corresponding descriptions.

The two input rasters must have the same number of rows and columns. All of the values in the raster data must be present
in the classification key. Handled errors such as failing to meet those criteria will be reported to the user in an error
window.

This program calculates global and per-class results. The global results consist of an error matrix of landcover classes and 
the overall percent correct. The per-class results are a contingency table of presence and absence as well as the precision,
recall and f1-score statistics. These results are put into a StringBuilder which is then put into a JTextPane in a JFrame that
will display to the user, as well as being saved to a text file.